OL,3,CWelfare cuts: 'It is going to change
OL,4,Cmy life even more for the worst'
OL,6,FGed continued: "It has taken over my
OL,7,Flife. I've got it for life and I have
OL,8,Fbeen told by a brain specialist that I
OL,9,Fcan't be on my own anymore because
OL,10,Fwhile I'm asleep, my brain can just
OL,11,Fstop and you won't wake up."
OL,13,FThe 52-year-old has now got one of his
OL,14,Fdaughters living with him and says his
OL,15,Fcondition has "taken over his life".
OL,17,FHe continued: "I struggle now getting
OL,18,Fabout and the tablets that I'm on
OL,19,Fcause dizziness as well as other side
OL,20,Feffects hitting me.
OL,1,W~k4j5 hw1~k4~c1 hw}h7}j7}      G3/9
